On Fri, 8 Aug 1997, Steve Gardner wrote in reply to the following:

> >I think the crucial difference between cheating in an ftf game and in
> >an email game (where this "cheating" is part of the game concept, at
> >least) is not in the physical or not physical manipulation of
> >tokens. The requirements for success differ: Secrecy and going
> >unnoticed long enough are needed in an ftf game; an email game needs
> >more elaborate (meta) rules, that in principle make some kinds of
> >"cheating" formally legal again. I guess that's what 116 is for. Of
> >course then it's not really cheating anymore, just playing cratively
> >and doing unexpected things, like MMM. And this should be encouraged,
> >IMHO.
> 
> Sympathy from this quarter. But how to achieve it? A suggestion,
> probably already being elaborated by others: first, switch to a
> convention under which Players can, in general, alter Nomic 
> Properties by posting to the Public Forum that they are doing so,
> but secondly, list exceptions to the general case by enumeration,
> not by abstract principle. By nature, abstract principles like those
> expressed in R1011 tend to be all-encompassing and so block potential
> avenues for creativity.
> 
> These are all questions of game design, not metaphysics, naturally.
> 
Perhaps both 116 and 1011 ought to be rewritten? I've been playing
around with something like the following:

Revised 116:

   Any action not otherwise prohibited or regulated by the Rules is
permissible. If a Player wishes to perform such an action, he/she may do
so by posting a message describing the action to the Public Forum. 
If a formal dispute arises as to the legality or effect of the action, it
is the sole responsibility of any interested parties to produce a
record of the timing and nature of the action allegedly performed.
If such evidence cannot be produced, the action shall have no legal
effect, insofar as that is consistent with the other Rules.
   If an action is regulated by other Rules, those Rules have precedence
regarding by whom and under what circumstances an action may be taken.

----------------------------------------------------------------- 

Vlad



