you to a duel? And if certain game events were contingent on those
actions, that I could trigger them by doing so?
  Now let's extend the situation. Let us assume a particular commodity
is owned by various Players but there are no Rules that specifically
allow or disallow trading them. I don't see any problem, in principle, 
in allowing such trades in the absence of the Rules. It merely involves
the free desires of the Players. You may not wish them to have the
power, but that can be resolved by passing a Rule, not by summarily
restricting their freedom of action. Similarly, I think Players should
be allowed to make enforceable Contracts in the absence of a specific
Rule, or of forming legal Groups for that matter. Now of course there
can be restrictions and regulations, but such a situation is at least
hypothetically possible, and I think desirable.
