Would the following assuage objections?

Revised 116:

   Any action not otherwise prohibited or regulated by the Rules and not
paradoxical or contrary to natural law is permissible. If a Player wishes to
perform such an action, he/she may do so by posting a message describing
the action to the Public Forum. If a formal dispute arises as to the
legality or effect of the action, it is the sole responsibility of any
interested parties to produce a record of the timing and nature of the
action allegedly performed. If such evidence cannot be produced, the
action shall have no legal effect, insofar as that is consistent with the
other Rules.
   If an action is regulated by other Rules, those Rules have precedence
regarding by whom and under what circumstances an action may be taken.

